#Concepts and Configuration

1. Configure your hostname

    - So that a public key certificate can be created from the self signed authority on a switch/router

2. Configure your domain name

    - ip domain-name nuggetlab.com

3. Generate your encryption keys (public/private keys)

    - crypto key generate rsa

    Size of modulus: 1024

4. Enable SSH version 2

    - ip ssh version 2

5. Create local user accounts

    - username paul {password|secret} cisco

6. Choose to allow telnet and/or SSH

    - line vty 0 15
    - transport input {ssh|telnet|all}
    - login local
